Text.SourceString: It’s hard to be upset when you’re this relaxed.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to be upset when you’re this relaxed.

Text.SourceString: One of my students lives in this area.//He lives down the road, in that house. You see?
Text.LocalizedString: One of my students lives in this area.//He lives down the road, in that house. You see?

Text.SourceString: I’m not sure what’s in here, but I can taste the flavor all the way to my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not sure what’s in here, but I can taste the flavor all the way to my bones.

Text.SourceString: It must be the view.//<portrait=normal>I have a feeling even burned food would taste delicious here.
Text.LocalizedString: It must be the view.//<portrait=normal>I have a feeling even burned food would taste delicious here.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NPCName>Leah</> and I could spend more time together, like we did when she was younger. But she has other interests these days.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NPCName>Leah</> and I could spend more time together, like we did when she was younger. But she has other interests these days.

Text.SourceString: Her mother and I got together too young.//We both grew.//Neither of us was the same person when we parted ways.
Text.LocalizedString: Her mother and I got together too young.//We both grew.//Neither of us was the same person when we parted ways.

Text.SourceString: I can mostly do everything myself, but it’s nice to have some help.//Who’s better at knowing where to find reading material than <NPCName>Ms. Millie</> herself?
Text.LocalizedString: I can mostly do everything myself, but it’s nice to have some help.//Who’s better at knowing where to find reading material than <NPCName>Ms. Millie</> herself?

Text.SourceString: It’s been a while since I’ve read a great series.//The last one that held my attention must have been the Peppity Witch Adventures.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been a while since I’ve read a great series.//The last one that held my attention must have been the Peppity Witch Adventures.

Text.SourceString: What do you mean you’ve never heard of the Peppity Witch Adventures?!//<portrait=happy>Get out of here!
Text.LocalizedString: What do you mean you’ve never heard of the Peppity Witch Adventures?!//<portrait=happy>Get out of here!

Text.SourceString: I always see <NPCName>Millie</> working here. She rarely leaves her area…//She’s very focused.
Text.LocalizedString: I always see <NPCName>Millie</> working here. She rarely leaves her area…//She’s very focused.

Text.SourceString: I have to check out the museum and see if they’ve added more artifacts.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to check out the museum and see if they’ve added more artifacts.

Text.SourceString: I’m jealous of you adventurous folk who move to the island. Wide-eyed, fresh-faced, all ready to start your hero’s journey.//What a great feeling that must be.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m jealous of you adventurous folk who move to the island. Wide-eyed, fresh-faced, all ready to start your hero’s journey.//What a great feeling that must be.

Text.SourceString: So there I was, facing off with the alligator deep in the jungle. I was tired and hungry, but the gator looked hungrier.//I managed to escape…but not before he took my arm with him.
Text.LocalizedString: So there I was, facing off with the alligator deep in the jungle. I was tired and hungry, but the gator looked hungrier.//I managed to escape…but not before he took my arm with him.

Text.SourceString: Nah, I’m just pulling your leg – or maybe your arm! The kids just love that story.
Text.LocalizedString: Nah, I’m just pulling your leg – or maybe your arm! The kids just love that story.

Text.SourceString: It feels like a good day to drink a glass of wine and read some Dolstoy.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like a good day to drink a glass of wine and read some Dolstoy.

Text.SourceString: Feel free to join me whenever it strikes your fancy. I’m always happy to have someone to talk about Dolstoy with.
Text.LocalizedString: Feel free to join me whenever it strikes your fancy. I’m always happy to have someone to talk about Dolstoy with.

Text.SourceString: Like I always say, <PlayerName>$player</>, it doesn’t matter what you read, as long as you keep reading.
Text.LocalizedString: Like I always say, <PlayerName>$player</>, it doesn’t matter what you read, as long as you keep reading.

Text.SourceString: What’s keeping your attention these days?//Adventure books? Romance novels? The funny pages in the paper?//If only newspapers were as widespread as they used to be.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s keeping your attention these days?//Adventure books? Romance novels? The funny pages in the paper?//If only newspapers were as widespread as they used to be.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I can’t make heads or tails of what <NPCName>Leah’s</> saying.//It’s like she’s speaking another language.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I can’t make heads or tails of what <NPCName>Leah’s</> saying.//It’s like she’s speaking another language.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should ask <NPCName>Valentina</> if she can interpret for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should ask <NPCName>Valentina</> if she can interpret for me.

Text.SourceString: Have you been up to the mansion yet? If not, you should really take a look. <NPCName>Ling</> and I keep the most wonderful library inside.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you been up to the mansion yet? If not, you should really take a look. <NPCName>Ling</> and I keep the most wonderful library inside.

Text.SourceString: I promise it’s not nearly as fancy as the name implies.//That’s just what the folks around here have always called it.
Text.LocalizedString: I promise it’s not nearly as fancy as the name implies.//That’s just what the folks around here have always called it.

Text.SourceString: Oh good. It’s almost time for another cup of coffee!//<portrait=normal>There’s just something about hot drinks that really keeps me going.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh good. It’s almost time for another cup of coffee!//<portrait=normal>There’s just something about hot drinks that really keeps me going.

Text.SourceString: If your coffee is thick and strong, you can do no wrong!
Text.LocalizedString: If your coffee is thick and strong, you can do no wrong!

Text.SourceString: I wish I could stay and chat, <PlayerName>$player</>, but I’ve got a few tests to grade.//Let’s take it easy over some coffee another day.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could stay and chat, <PlayerName>$player</>, but I’ve got a few tests to grade.//Let’s take it easy over some coffee another day.

Text.SourceString: I could see <NPCName>Valentina</> as the protagonist of a book.//She’s sharp as a tack – the best in her class, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: I could see <NPCName>Valentina</> as the protagonist of a book.//She’s sharp as a tack – the best in her class, actually.

Text.SourceString: That <NPCName>Suki</> knows what she’s doing. I need to ask about her organizational methods.//And <NPCName>Antonio</>, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: That <NPCName>Suki</> knows what she’s doing. I need to ask about her organizational methods.//And <NPCName>Antonio</>, of course.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait to teach the kids about <Italic>The Mediocre Gatsby</> and <Italic>The Color Violet</>. They’re not quite old enough to read those, but they’ll be there eventually.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to teach the kids about <Italic>The Mediocre Gatsby</> and <Italic>The Color Violet</>. They’re not quite old enough to read those, but they’ll be there eventually.

Text.SourceString: There’s so much to be learned from literature.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so much to be learned from literature.

Text.SourceString: Questions don’t normally stump me, but the other day <NPCName>Ling</> asked me which author, living or dead, I would eat lunch with. I started at the wall like a nitwit for at least half an hour.
Text.LocalizedString: Questions don’t normally stump me, but the other day <NPCName>Ling</> asked me which author, living or dead, I would eat lunch with. I started at the wall like a nitwit for at least half an hour.

Text.SourceString: There’s too many to choose from! I’d rather have a five-minute snack with ten of them than a full lunch with any one person.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s too many to choose from! I’d rather have a five-minute snack with ten of them than a full lunch with any one person.

Text.SourceString: How’s life on the farm going, <PlayerName>$player</>? Any new plotlines in your life?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s life on the farm going, <PlayerName>$player</>? Any new plotlines in your life?

Text.SourceString: I do all the curriculum design for Starlet Town Elementary.//Everyone has a strong opinion about what they want their kids to learn.
Text.LocalizedString: I do all the curriculum design for Starlet Town Elementary.//Everyone has a strong opinion about what they want their kids to learn.

Text.SourceString: I usually stick to the tried-and-true.//<portrait=normal>If it worked for me, it’ll work for them!
Text.LocalizedString: I usually stick to the tried-and-true.//<portrait=normal>If it worked for me, it’ll work for them!

Text.SourceString: I love spending my evenings with <NPCName>Ling</>. The two of us sit by the fire and talk about what we learned that day or what new discoveries she made in her work.//<portrait=normal>I don’t see how life could get better than this.
Text.LocalizedString: I love spending my evenings with <NPCName>Ling</>. The two of us sit by the fire and talk about what we learned that day or what new discoveries she made in her work.//<portrait=normal>I don’t see how life could get better than this.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling’s</> been telling me about all the plastic she’s found in the ocean recently.//The country needs to pass some stricter laws about all that pollution.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling’s</> been telling me about all the plastic she’s found in the ocean recently.//The country needs to pass some stricter laws about all that pollution.

Text.SourceString: If people knew it was against the law to litter, maybe they’d think twice about it.
Text.LocalizedString: If people knew it was against the law to litter, maybe they’d think twice about it.

Text.SourceString: My goodness, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look exhausted.//I know farming is hard, but I didn’t think it was quite that bad.
Text.LocalizedString: My goodness, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look exhausted.//I know farming is hard, but I didn’t think it was quite that bad.

Text.SourceString: Bless your heart. Go sit down and have a nice cup of coffee. It’ll perk you right back up, I promise!
Text.LocalizedString: Bless your heart. Go sit down and have a nice cup of coffee. It’ll perk you right back up, I promise!

Text.SourceString: It feels like a good day to drink a glass of wine and read some Dolstoy.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like a good day to drink a glass of wine and read some Dolstoy.

Text.SourceString: Feel free to join me whenever it strikes your fancy. I’m always happy to have someone to talk about Dolstoy with.
Text.LocalizedString: Feel free to join me whenever it strikes your fancy. I’m always happy to have someone to talk about Dolstoy with.

Text.SourceString: I could see <NPCName>Valentina</> as the protagonist of a book.//She’s sharp as a tack – the best in her class, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: I could see <NPCName>Valentina</> as the protagonist of a book.//She’s sharp as a tack – the best in her class, actually.

Text.SourceString: That <NPCName>Suki</> knows what she’s doing. I need to ask about her organizational methods.//And <NPCName>Antonio</>, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: That <NPCName>Suki</> knows what she’s doing. I need to ask about her organizational methods.//And <NPCName>Antonio</>, of course.

Text.SourceString: The kids are always hard to teach on Fridays.//They want to skip right past their lessons and go straight to the weekend.
Text.LocalizedString: The kids are always hard to teach on Fridays.//They want to skip right past their lessons and go straight to the weekend.

Text.SourceString: One thing that’s great about being a teacher is I always get weekends off.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing that’s great about being a teacher is I always get weekends off.

Text.SourceString: Have you been up to the mansion yet?//If not, you should really take a look. <NPCName>Ling</> and I keep the most wonderful library inside.//It’s on the second floor of the house, in my office.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you been up to the mansion yet?//If not, you should really take a look. <NPCName>Ling</> and I keep the most wonderful library inside.//It’s on the second floor of the house, in my office.

Text.SourceString: I promise it’s not nearly as fancy as the name implies.//That’s just what the folks around here have always called it.
Text.LocalizedString: I promise it’s not nearly as fancy as the name implies.//That’s just what the folks around here have always called it.

Text.SourceString: Like I always say, <PlayerName>$player</>, it doesn’t matter what you read, as long as you keep reading.
Text.LocalizedString: Like I always say, <PlayerName>$player</>, it doesn’t matter what you read, as long as you keep reading.

Text.SourceString: What’s keeping your attention these days?//Adventure books? Romance novels? The funny pages in the paper?//If only newspapers were as widespread as they used to be.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s keeping your attention these days?//Adventure books? Romance novels? The funny pages in the paper?//If only newspapers were as widespread as they used to be.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah’s</> a pretty impressive photographer.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah’s</> a pretty impressive photographer.

Text.SourceString: I hear she has quite the following on social media, too.//Her mother and I always knew she’d be an artist.
Text.LocalizedString: I hear she has quite the following on social media, too.//Her mother and I always knew she’d be an artist.

Text.SourceString: I made the mistake of reading past my bedtime last night.//As fun as it was, these aging bones can’t handle late nights like they used to.
Text.LocalizedString: I made the mistake of reading past my bedtime last night.//As fun as it was, these aging bones can’t handle late nights like they used to.

Text.SourceString: My goodness, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look exhausted.//I know farming is hard, but I didn’t think it was quite that bad.
Text.LocalizedString: My goodness, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look exhausted.//I know farming is hard, but I didn’t think it was quite that bad.

Text.SourceString: Bless your heart. Go sit down and have a nice cup of coffee. It’ll perk you right back up, I promise!
Text.LocalizedString: Bless your heart. Go sit down and have a nice cup of coffee. It’ll perk you right back up, I promise!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling’s</> been telling me about all the plastic she’s found in the ocean recently.//The country needs to pass some stricter laws about all that pollution.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling’s</> been telling me about all the plastic she’s found in the ocean recently.//The country needs to pass some stricter laws about all that pollution.

Text.SourceString: If people knew it was against the law to litter, maybe they’d think twice about it.
Text.LocalizedString: If people knew it was against the law to litter, maybe they’d think twice about it.

Text.SourceString: What sort of story do you think you’ll write while you’re on Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What sort of story do you think you’ll write while you’re on Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I don’t mean literally writing.//Everyone writes a story simply by living.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mean literally writing.//Everyone writes a story simply by living.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been thinking about starting an after-school reading club at Starlet Town Elementary.//Do you think the kids would like that?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been thinking about starting an after-school reading club at Starlet Town Elementary.//Do you think the kids would like that?

Text.SourceString: They’d get to read fun stuff, but they’d also get extra reading practice.//I think it’s a win-win.
Text.LocalizedString: They’d get to read fun stuff, but they’d also get extra reading practice.//I think it’s a win-win.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling</> keeps threatening to use some of my books as kindling if I don’t read them.//I told her I’m getting there, I’m getting there! Or maybe I’ll just read all of them when I retire.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling</> keeps threatening to use some of my books as kindling if I don’t read them.//I told her I’m getting there, I’m getting there! Or maybe I’ll just read all of them when I retire.

Text.SourceString: Buying books and actually reading them are two different activities, I’ve learned.
Text.LocalizedString: Buying books and actually reading them are two different activities, I’ve learned.

Text.SourceString: I do a unit on conservation and the environment every year for my class.//The kids are too young to understand the scientific details behind it, but if I can get them to recognize throwing trash in the ocean is bad, I’ve done my job.
Text.LocalizedString: I do a unit on conservation and the environment every year for my class.//The kids are too young to understand the scientific details behind it, but if I can get them to recognize throwing trash in the ocean is bad, I’ve done my job.

Text.SourceString: The animal and plant species on Coral Island are so interesting.//I know <NPCName>Ling</> moved to the island because there are species here she couldn’t study anywhere else.
Text.LocalizedString: The animal and plant species on Coral Island are so interesting.//I know <NPCName>Ling</> moved to the island because there are species here she couldn’t study anywhere else.

Text.SourceString: Spring always symbolizes new beginnings in literature. It’s the season of love, renewal, and growth.//<portrait=happy>Or the season of pollen, if you’re allergic.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring always symbolizes new beginnings in literature. It’s the season of love, renewal, and growth.//<portrait=happy>Or the season of pollen, if you’re allergic.

Text.SourceString: What a year for blooms! Spring always looks good on Coral Island, but this year seems even more spectacular than usual.
Text.LocalizedString: What a year for blooms! Spring always looks good on Coral Island, but this year seems even more spectacular than usual.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Leah</> taking some very artsy photos of flowers the other day.//It made me happy someone is preserving and sharing the island’s beauty.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Leah</> taking some very artsy photos of flowers the other day.//It made me happy someone is preserving and sharing the island’s beauty.

Text.SourceString: It’s almost time for my yearly library declutter!//Time to put away all the books I’ve been reading over the Winter and replace them with some brand-spanking-new titles.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s almost time for my yearly library declutter!//Time to put away all the books I’ve been reading over the Winter and replace them with some brand-spanking-new titles.

Text.SourceString: The season of salt and sweat is upon us! I’m always grateful for every one of Coral Island’s seasons.
Text.LocalizedString: The season of salt and sweat is upon us! I’m always grateful for every one of Coral Island’s seasons.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> loves to sit on the beach in Summer.//I’ve never actually seen her get in the water, though.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> loves to sit on the beach in Summer.//I’ve never actually seen her get in the water, though.

Text.SourceString: Oh, how I love Fall! Authors have sung its praises since what feels like the beginning of time. It’s the season of crisp breezes and veggies aplenty.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, how I love Fall! Authors have sung its praises since what feels like the beginning of time. It’s the season of crisp breezes and veggies aplenty.

Text.SourceString: Reading in front of kids sets a good example for them.//If they see you reading, they’re more likely to try it for themselves.
Text.LocalizedString: Reading in front of kids sets a good example for them.//If they see you reading, they’re more likely to try it for themselves.

Text.SourceString: I get the feeling this year’s harvest will be a bountiful one.//Thinking about all the concoctions I’ll be eating soon makes my mouth water!
Text.LocalizedString: I get the feeling this year’s harvest will be a bountiful one.//Thinking about all the concoctions I’ll be eating soon makes my mouth water!

Text.SourceString: Sometimes the Fall harvest comes a little later than usual, but all we can do is wait. There’s no rushing nature.//She knows what she’s doing.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes the Fall harvest comes a little later than usual, but all we can do is wait. There’s no rushing nature.//She knows what she’s doing.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling</> isn’t a big fan of the water temperature this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling</> isn’t a big fan of the water temperature this time of year.

Text.SourceString: I try to have a hot mug of tea and a blanket ready for her when she gets home from work.//It’s the least I can do.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to have a hot mug of tea and a blanket ready for her when she gets home from work.//It’s the least I can do.

Text.SourceString: The mansion gets quite drafty in Winter, so we have to plug all its cracks and keep the heat going all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: The mansion gets quite drafty in Winter, so we have to plug all its cracks and keep the heat going all the time.

Text.SourceString: Those help a lot, but you still need a blanket if you go too far away from the main room.
Text.LocalizedString: Those help a lot, but you still need a blanket if you go too far away from the main room.

Text.SourceString: It’s amazing to think the same water that flows through our rivers and lakes ends up in the sky as rain.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s amazing to think the same water that flows through our rivers and lakes ends up in the sky as rain.

Text.SourceString: Mother Nature is a sight to behold.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother Nature is a sight to behold.

Text.SourceString: If it keeps raining like this, the kids won’t be having recess anytime soon.
Text.LocalizedString: If it keeps raining like this, the kids won’t be having recess anytime soon.

Text.SourceString: This has turned into a bit of a chilly rain. I’d better get home soon.
Text.LocalizedString: This has turned into a bit of a chilly rain. I’d better get home soon.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> hates rainy days. She says they mess up her hair.//<portrait=happy>I say just let the rain give it a wash. It’s one less thing you have to do!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> hates rainy days. She says they mess up her hair.//<portrait=happy>I say just let the rain give it a wash. It’s one less thing you have to do!

Text.SourceString: I think <NPCName>Valentina</> said she wanted to play volleyball tonight.//Looks like that’s not going to work out in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I think <NPCName>Valentina</> said she wanted to play volleyball tonight.//Looks like that’s not going to work out in this weather.

Text.SourceString: Watching the rain run down the windows makes me feel like a wise old author.
Text.LocalizedString: Watching the rain run down the windows makes me feel like a wise old author.

Text.SourceString: What do you use to keep the rain off you? A raincoat? An umbrella?//Do you just run through it and hope for the best?//<portrait=happy>The kids like that option.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you use to keep the rain off you? A raincoat? An umbrella?//Do you just run through it and hope for the best?//<portrait=happy>The kids like that option.

Text.SourceString: Can you imagine what life would be like if it could rain indoors?//It’d be the darndest thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you imagine what life would be like if it could rain indoors?//It’d be the darndest thing.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should write a novel about that.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should write a novel about that.

Text.SourceString: Rain is always a nice sound to fall asleep to. I won’t need to use my sound machine tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain is always a nice sound to fall asleep to. I won’t need to use my sound machine tonight.

Text.SourceString: These are the nights wine was made for. It’s one of life’s greatest pleasures.
Text.LocalizedString: These are the nights wine was made for. It’s one of life’s greatest pleasures.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Suki</> running in the rain earlier.//How does she do it? There’s no way on this green earth I could motivate myself to get wet and sweaty.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Suki</> running in the rain earlier.//How does she do it? There’s no way on this green earth I could motivate myself to get wet and sweaty.

Text.SourceString: We’re two very different people.//You’ve gotta respect her discipline.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re two very different people.//You’ve gotta respect her discipline.

Text.SourceString: Now, this is a gale! You ought to call it a day in this type of weather, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, this is a gale! You ought to call it a day in this type of weather, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: If I’m not careful, my tie’s going to blow away out here.
Text.LocalizedString: If I’m not careful, my tie’s going to blow away out here.

Text.SourceString: This one’s my favorite too! I can’t let it blow away.
Text.LocalizedString: This one’s my favorite too! I can’t let it blow away.

Text.SourceString: You ought to head home, <PlayerName>$player</>.//These sorts of storms are even more dangerous at night.
Text.LocalizedString: You ought to head home, <PlayerName>$player</>.//These sorts of storms are even more dangerous at night.

Text.SourceString: You ought to head home, <PlayerName>$player</>.//These sorts of storms are even more dangerous at night.
Text.LocalizedString: You ought to head home, <PlayerName>$player</>.//These sorts of storms are even more dangerous at night.

Text.SourceString: I hope your work is over soon, <PlayerName>$player</>.//These sorts of storms were made for curling up at home, not running around outside like a headless chicken.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope your work is over soon, <PlayerName>$player</>.//These sorts of storms were made for curling up at home, not running around outside like a headless chicken.

Text.SourceString: The crack of thunder is such a majestic sound. Unless it’s too loud, and it makes all the kids in your class jump.
Text.LocalizedString: The crack of thunder is such a majestic sound. Unless it’s too loud, and it makes all the kids in your class jump.

Text.SourceString: I like falling asleep to the sound of rain, but this is a little too much.
Text.LocalizedString: I like falling asleep to the sound of rain, but this is a little too much.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ll be able to sleep tonight in weather like this.//Looks like another long night of reading.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ll be able to sleep tonight in weather like this.//Looks like another long night of reading.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind that one bit, but I’ll definitely be tired tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind that one bit, but I’ll definitely be tired tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: What a jolly great day! Snow has a way of making everyone feel like a kid again.
Text.LocalizedString: What a jolly great day! Snow has a way of making everyone feel like a kid again.

Text.SourceString: My class challenged me to a snowball fight the other day.//Naturally, they won. I just can’t move as fast as they can.
Text.LocalizedString: My class challenged me to a snowball fight the other day.//Naturally, they won. I just can’t move as fast as they can.

Text.SourceString: Looks like all the snow is starting to freeze over. Cold enough out here for ya, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Looks like all the snow is starting to freeze over. Cold enough out here for ya, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: As much as I’d love to talk with you, you caught me on my way home. Let’s chat another time when I’m warmer.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I’d love to talk with you, you caught me on my way home. Let’s chat another time when I’m warmer.

Text.SourceString: You’d think the kids who live around here would hate snow, but they can’t get enough of it.//That really tickles me.
Text.LocalizedString: You’d think the kids who live around here would hate snow, but they can’t get enough of it.//That really tickles me.

Text.SourceString: It must have been awful to be an old-timey author in Winter.//No central heat, having to keep a steady supply of firewood in the house…
Text.LocalizedString: It must have been awful to be an old-timey author in Winter.//No central heat, having to keep a steady supply of firewood in the house…

Text.SourceString: No wonder everyone who lived a hundred years ago was sad.
Text.LocalizedString: No wonder everyone who lived a hundred years ago was sad.

Text.SourceString: We’re in the most quiet and contemplative environment, the snowy night.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re in the most quiet and contemplative environment, the snowy night.

Text.SourceString: Can you feel yourself getting smarter and more thoughtful?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you feel yourself getting smarter and more thoughtful?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> loved the snow when she was a little girl, but now she just prefers to stay inside.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> loved the snow when she was a little girl, but now she just prefers to stay inside.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Randy</> looks like he’s busy with teaching.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Randy</> looks like he’s busy with teaching.]

Text.SourceString: You wouldn’t happen to know where my lesson plans went, would you? I just set them down here a moment ago.
Text.LocalizedString: You wouldn’t happen to know where my lesson plans went, would you? I just set them down here a moment ago.

Text.SourceString: By golly, if those kids are pranking me again…
Text.LocalizedString: By golly, if those kids are pranking me again…

Text.SourceString: Looking out into a classroom is like looking into a crystal ball.//You can see what the future holds with each and every kid in your class.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking out into a classroom is like looking into a crystal ball.//You can see what the future holds with each and every kid in your class.

Text.SourceString: It’s a wonderful – and terrifying – feeling.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a wonderful – and terrifying – feeling.

Text.SourceString: Look at this place.//I’m so lucky I get to work here every day.
Text.LocalizedString: Look at this place.//I’m so lucky I get to work here every day.

Text.SourceString: Well, I didn’t quite finish grading those papers last night, but that’s okay.//I’ll just tell the kids I decided to take the night off.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I didn’t quite finish grading those papers last night, but that’s okay.//I’ll just tell the kids I decided to take the night off.

Text.SourceString: It’s good to take breaks here and there.//It’s good for your mental health.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s good to take breaks here and there.//It’s good for your mental health.

Text.SourceString: What kind of skills does it take to be a farmer? You probably have to track your resources and be decent with money too.//I bet you have to know how to care for animals and how to deal with people when you sell your crops.
Text.LocalizedString: What kind of skills does it take to be a farmer? You probably have to track your resources and be decent with money too.//I bet you have to know how to care for animals and how to deal with people when you sell your crops.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe how beautiful this town has become.//It seems like only yesterday it was a tiny little place in the middle of nowhere.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe how beautiful this town has become.//It seems like only yesterday it was a tiny little place in the middle of nowhere.

Text.SourceString: Watching kids run through the yard makes me feel young again.
Text.LocalizedString: Watching kids run through the yard makes me feel young again.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I try to chase them, but they’re always faster than me. Maybe I’d be faster if I cut back on the wine.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I try to chase them, but they’re always faster than me. Maybe I’d be faster if I cut back on the wine.

Text.SourceString: On warm nights, there’s nothing better than being here with a book, taking in the atmosphere.//It’s a right pleasant way to spend an evening.
Text.LocalizedString: On warm nights, there’s nothing better than being here with a book, taking in the atmosphere.//It’s a right pleasant way to spend an evening.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen all the books they have here?//It’s enough to make my poor old heart sing with joy.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen all the books they have here?//It’s enough to make my poor old heart sing with joy.

Text.SourceString: I always take my class on a yearly field trip to the library.//It helps show them it’s a fun, useful place, even if they can just look everything up online.
Text.LocalizedString: I always take my class on a yearly field trip to the library.//It helps show them it’s a fun, useful place, even if they can just look everything up online.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Millie</> and I have actually been close friends for a long time.//She always lets me check out more books than I’m supposed to.//<portrait=happy>That’s the only rule I ever break!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Millie</> and I have actually been close friends for a long time.//She always lets me check out more books than I’m supposed to.//<portrait=happy>That’s the only rule I ever break!

Text.SourceString: People often think berries are just small fruits that we pick from bushes or short plants.//But avocados are in fact berries, and they grow on trees.
Text.LocalizedString: People often think berries are just small fruits that we pick from bushes or short plants.//But avocados are in fact berries, and they grow on trees.

Text.SourceString: And unlike blueberries, strawberries are botanically not berries!//<portrait=normal>It’s because strawberries come from a flower that has many ovaries.
Text.LocalizedString: And unlike blueberries, strawberries are botanically not berries!//<portrait=normal>It’s because strawberries come from a flower that has many ovaries.

Text.SourceString: The kids love to study plants.//<portrait=happy>I hope it’d be okay to take them to your farm sometime, you know, to see some seasonal plants in real life. What do you say?
Text.LocalizedString: The kids love to study plants.//<portrait=happy>I hope it’d be okay to take them to your farm sometime, you know, to see some seasonal plants in real life. What do you say?

Text.SourceString: I’m sorry if I talk too much about plants. I get carried away easily.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sorry if I talk too much about plants. I get carried away easily.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about my arm. I’m afraid there’s no shocking story behind it.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about my arm. I’m afraid there’s no shocking story behind it.

Text.SourceString: I was born with only a partial left arm.//Science has come so far since that day, and I’m grateful to have this arm.
Text.LocalizedString: I was born with only a partial left arm.//Science has come so far since that day, and I’m grateful to have this arm.

Text.SourceString: Botanically, an ovary is a reproductive organ that later ripens into a fruit.//Isn’t that interesting?
Text.LocalizedString: Botanically, an ovary is a reproductive organ that later ripens into a fruit.//Isn’t that interesting?

Text.SourceString: Would you consider a tomato a fruit or a vegetable, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’m asking your professional opinion, as someone who deals with these sorts of crops every day.
Text.LocalizedString: Would you consider a tomato a fruit or a vegetable, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’m asking your professional opinion, as someone who deals with these sorts of crops every day.

Text.SourceString: I’ve spent my whole life teaching youth.//It keeps you young, being around young minds all day. But it has its hardships, you know, just like any other job.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve spent my whole life teaching youth.//It keeps you young, being around young minds all day. But it has its hardships, you know, just like any other job.

Text.SourceString: Extra books and project costs add up. They can be expensive.
Text.LocalizedString: Extra books and project costs add up. They can be expensive.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I think about whether I did the right thing keeping <NPCName>Leah</> here on Coral Island. I don’t want her to feel stuck.//Just like her mother did.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I think about whether I did the right thing keeping <NPCName>Leah</> here on Coral Island. I don’t want her to feel stuck.//Just like her mother did.

Text.SourceString: Things were rough during <NPCName>Leah’s</> childhood, since her mom traveled every chance she got.//But I couldn’t fault her for that. This island wasn’t for her.
Text.LocalizedString: Things were rough during <NPCName>Leah’s</> childhood, since her mom traveled every chance she got.//But I couldn’t fault her for that. This island wasn’t for her.

Text.SourceString: Can’t force someone to stay, <PlayerName>$player</>.//But when her mother would leave, <NPCName>Leah</> would always get so upset on the first night, and she’d lose sleep over it.//Broke my heart every time.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t force someone to stay, <PlayerName>$player</>.//But when her mother would leave, <NPCName>Leah</> would always get so upset on the first night, and she’d lose sleep over it.//Broke my heart every time.

Text.SourceString: Nothing changes. Fake arm or not, I’m still doing the exact same things.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing changes. Fake arm or not, I’m still doing the exact same things.

Text.SourceString: Right. Except now, I won’t start shivering if I hold a snowball too long. Hah!
Text.LocalizedString: Right. Except now, I won’t start shivering if I hold a snowball too long. Hah!

Text.SourceString: I’m proud we’re teaching kids about the effect trash has on the environment.//Getting the little things they can do to help to stick in their minds is tricky, but hopefully, it’s all worth it in the end.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m proud we’re teaching kids about the effect trash has on the environment.//Getting the little things they can do to help to stick in their minds is tricky, but hopefully, it’s all worth it in the end.

Text.SourceString: We went to the beach last Summer. The whole class went.//<portrait=normal>We made sure to take our trash home from a beach day. Little things like that – they’re important.
Text.LocalizedString: We went to the beach last Summer. The whole class went.//<portrait=normal>We made sure to take our trash home from a beach day. Little things like that – they’re important.

Text.SourceString: What is it with being friends and sharing recipes here?//I’m not complaining. I think it’s great.
Text.LocalizedString: What is it with being friends and sharing recipes here?//I’m not complaining. I think it’s great.

Text.SourceString: I started chatting with <NPCName>Suki</> about <NPCName>Valentina</> to keep her updated on <NPCName>Valentina’s</> progress more closely.//<portrait=normal>And the next thing I knew, she mailed me a recipe for her secret green smoothies. Generous, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: I started chatting with <NPCName>Suki</> about <NPCName>Valentina</> to keep her updated on <NPCName>Valentina’s</> progress more closely.//<portrait=normal>And the next thing I knew, she mailed me a recipe for her secret green smoothies. Generous, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I wish things with <NPCName>Leah’s</> mom had been better.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish things with <NPCName>Leah’s</> mom had been better.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mean we should have stayed together. No, that part was over long before we separated. I don’t regret that.//I regret the toll it took on <NPCName>Leah</>.//<portrait=concerned>With the fights. With the yelling. She’s become even more estranged from her mother now.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mean we should have stayed together. No, that part was over long before we separated. I don’t regret that.//I regret the toll it took on <NPCName>Leah</>.//<portrait=concerned>With the fights. With the yelling. She’s become even more estranged from her mother now.

Text.SourceString: Maybe if I’d tried harder with her mom, she wouldn’t have left <NPCName>Leah</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe if I’d tried harder with her mom, she wouldn’t have left <NPCName>Leah</>.

Text.SourceString: I know how hard it’s been for <NPCName>Leah</>…my divorce.//I hope someday she can forgive me.
Text.LocalizedString: I know how hard it’s been for <NPCName>Leah</>…my divorce.//I hope someday she can forgive me.

Text.SourceString: Some shows can get pretty out there. A zombie apocalypse, talking plants. Hmm. What else?
Text.LocalizedString: Some shows can get pretty out there. A zombie apocalypse, talking plants. Hmm. What else?

Text.SourceString: Not my thing. I stick to sports.
Text.LocalizedString: Not my thing. I stick to sports.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, we can’t wait around for a green light, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Taking the initiative is hard, but maybe worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, we can’t wait around for a green light, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Taking the initiative is hard, but maybe worth it.

Text.SourceString: If you think you need to do something, you may need to “green-light” yourself, as long as it doesn’t hurt others.//No point in waiting around.
Text.LocalizedString: If you think you need to do something, you may need to “green-light” yourself, as long as it doesn’t hurt others.//No point in waiting around.

Text.SourceString: I’m happy with my life in general, with how things have…played out.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m happy with my life in general, with how things have…played out.

Text.SourceString: I hope you feel the same way about your decision to move here.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you feel the same way about your decision to move here.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to my Sunday dinner with <NPCName>Leah</>.//The food is always wonderful, but more than that, I’m more excited to find out about her week.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to my Sunday dinner with <NPCName>Leah</>.//The food is always wonderful, but more than that, I’m more excited to find out about her week.

Text.SourceString: If she ever decided to live abroad like her mother, I’d support her 100 percent.//I know I wouldn’t lose her. She’d keep me in the loop. She wants me in her life.
Text.LocalizedString: If she ever decided to live abroad like her mother, I’d support her 100 percent.//I know I wouldn’t lose her. She’d keep me in the loop. She wants me in her life.

Text.SourceString: I simply can’t ask for more. My heart is full.
Text.LocalizedString: I simply can’t ask for more. My heart is full.

Text.SourceString: I feel worn out, and it’s only Wednesday.//One of those days, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel worn out, and it’s only Wednesday.//One of those days, I think.

Text.SourceString: I have to visit my friends at the shack soon. It’s been so long since I’ve caught up with them.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to visit my friends at the shack soon. It’s been so long since I’ve caught up with them.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a big fisher myself. So, I usually don’t fish, unlike <NPCName>Sunny</> or the mayor.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a big fisher myself. So, I usually don’t fish, unlike <NPCName>Sunny</> or the mayor.

Text.SourceString: I won’t say no to a fishing trip, though. I just can’t go too long while school’s open.
Text.LocalizedString: I won’t say no to a fishing trip, though. I just can’t go too long while school’s open.

Text.SourceString: I’ll always love <NPCName>Leah’s</> mother.//If it weren’t for her, I wouldn’t have <NPCName>Leah</>, after all.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll always love <NPCName>Leah’s</> mother.//If it weren’t for her, I wouldn’t have <NPCName>Leah</>, after all.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to disturb <NPCName>Leah</> with this, but I’ve been reaching out to her mother.//Trying to build a relationship, for<NPCName>Leah’s</> sake.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to disturb <NPCName>Leah</> with this, but I’ve been reaching out to her mother.//Trying to build a relationship, for<NPCName>Leah’s</> sake.

Text.SourceString: But I’m getting the cold shoulder. I kept my mouth shut.//I don’t want to trash her image in our daughter’s eyes.
Text.LocalizedString: But I’m getting the cold shoulder. I kept my mouth shut.//I don’t want to trash her image in our daughter’s eyes.

Text.SourceString: Might be time for me to get new boots.//These are starting to hurt.
Text.LocalizedString: Might be time for me to get new boots.//These are starting to hurt.

Text.SourceString: I walked here this morning, and my feet are aching. If you think about it, it isn’t that far!
Text.LocalizedString: I walked here this morning, and my feet are aching. If you think about it, it isn’t that far!

Text.SourceString: When things are hard, I look to literature for advice.//Different books may give different answers, but they all lead somewhere good.
Text.LocalizedString: When things are hard, I look to literature for advice.//Different books may give different answers, but they all lead somewhere good.

Text.SourceString: Between you and me, I’m worried about <NPCName>Leah</>.//She’s been growing more distant and distracted lately.
Text.LocalizedString: Between you and me, I’m worried about <NPCName>Leah</>.//She’s been growing more distant and distracted lately.

Text.SourceString: I talk to her, but she never says anything to me. It’s just “Yes, Dad” this and “No, Dad” that.//It’s probably been years since we’ve had a real conversation.
Text.LocalizedString: I talk to her, but she never says anything to me. It’s just “Yes, Dad” this and “No, Dad” that.//It’s probably been years since we’ve had a real conversation.

Text.SourceString: Every once in a while, I wonder what my ex is doing. <NPCName>Leah</> reminds me of her sometimes.//I just hope she’s happy.
Text.LocalizedString: Every once in a while, I wonder what my ex is doing. <NPCName>Leah</> reminds me of her sometimes.//I just hope she’s happy.

Text.SourceString: Oh, don’t worry about hiding that from <NPCName>Ling</>.//The two of us have talked about her before.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, don’t worry about hiding that from <NPCName>Ling</>.//The two of us have talked about her before.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Leah</> would be interested in visiting her mom sometime soon.//I hear she’s in town for an art show not too far from here.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Leah</> would be interested in visiting her mom sometime soon.//I hear she’s in town for an art show not too far from here.

Text.SourceString: She can pass on my regards too.
Text.LocalizedString: She can pass on my regards too.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever listen to anything while you read? Sometimes I like to put on soft ocean sounds in the background.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes, it makes me so relaxed I fall asleep!
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever listen to anything while you read? Sometimes I like to put on soft ocean sounds in the background.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes, it makes me so relaxed I fall asleep!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling</> jokes that instead of listening to fake ocean sounds, I could just walk down to the beach and listen to real ocean sounds.//The sun and my skin don’t get along, unfortunately.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling</> jokes that instead of listening to fake ocean sounds, I could just walk down to the beach and listen to real ocean sounds.//The sun and my skin don’t get along, unfortunately.

Text.SourceString: The mansion is a huge place, but when <NPCName>Leah</> is upset, it suddenly feels very, very small.//She has a way of filling up a place when she gets angry.
Text.LocalizedString: The mansion is a huge place, but when <NPCName>Leah</> is upset, it suddenly feels very, very small.//She has a way of filling up a place when she gets angry.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been thinking you’re quite a fine addition to the town, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been thinking you’re quite a fine addition to the town, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever thought about teaching in Starlet Town?//We’d love to have you! If all that farming business doesn’t work out, I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever thought about teaching in Starlet Town?//We’d love to have you! If all that farming business doesn’t work out, I mean.

Text.SourceString: Every once in a while, I’ll bring my class a little treat for behaving well.//<portrait=normal>Remind me next time, and I’ll save a little something for you too!
Text.LocalizedString: Every once in a while, I’ll bring my class a little treat for behaving well.//<portrait=normal>Remind me next time, and I’ll save a little something for you too!

Text.SourceString: It’s been a rough week. I think a nice glass of red wine and some Joan Austen are on tap tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been a rough week. I think a nice glass of red wine and some Joan Austen are on tap tonight.

Text.SourceString: Your fresh fruits and veggies would make great snacks for the kids!
Text.LocalizedString: Your fresh fruits and veggies would make great snacks for the kids!

Text.SourceString: I’ve always believed someone’s favorite book says a lot about them. What’s your favorite, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Hard question to answer, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve always believed someone’s favorite book says a lot about them. What’s your favorite, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Hard question to answer, huh?

Text.SourceString: I’m glad we met, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You’re a great friend.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad we met, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You’re a great friend.

Text.SourceString: There are some kids in here who are excelling, and a few who need some extra help.//That’s the same as always, though.
Text.LocalizedString: There are some kids in here who are excelling, and a few who need some extra help.//That’s the same as always, though.

Text.SourceString: Every kid learns differently. You just need to take your time with them.
Text.LocalizedString: Every kid learns differently. You just need to take your time with them.

Text.SourceString: I always make sure to include a unit on farming in my lesson plans.//<portrait=happy>Maybe we should get you in here to teach that one, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I always make sure to include a unit on farming in my lesson plans.//<portrait=happy>Maybe we should get you in here to teach that one, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Do you think you’d ever become a teacher? I could see you doing it.//You’re patient and a good listener.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think you’d ever become a teacher? I could see you doing it.//You’re patient and a good listener.

Text.SourceString: You’re also good at conflict resolution. That’s important when you’re working with kids.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re also good at conflict resolution. That’s important when you’re working with kids.

Text.SourceString: Do you come here a lot? I can see someone like you visiting this place quite a bit.//Bright, cheerful, full of energy. What a life to live.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you come here a lot? I can see someone like you visiting this place quite a bit.//Bright, cheerful, full of energy. What a life to live.

Text.SourceString: What sort of books are you reading right now, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I have to say I’m rather partial to the classics.
Text.LocalizedString: What sort of books are you reading right now, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I have to say I’m rather partial to the classics.

Text.SourceString: There are always lessons to be learned from those who came before us.
Text.LocalizedString: There are always lessons to be learned from those who came before us.

Text.SourceString: Back when <NPCName>Leah</> was little, I used to bring her here and let her wander for hours.//We’d pick out our favorite books and read together.
Text.LocalizedString: Back when <NPCName>Leah</> was little, I used to bring her here and let her wander for hours.//We’d pick out our favorite books and read together.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think she misses those days as much as I do.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think she misses those days as much as I do.

Text.SourceString: I make sure the kids play outside as much as I can. Being outside is good for both mental and physical health.//Especially now the snow has melted.
Text.LocalizedString: I make sure the kids play outside as much as I can. Being outside is good for both mental and physical health.//Especially now the snow has melted.

Text.SourceString: Enjoying Spring so far?
Text.LocalizedString: Enjoying Spring so far?

Text.SourceString: I don’t like wearing shorts.//Having to work outdoors often in Summer, mosquito bites are a concern for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like wearing shorts.//Having to work outdoors often in Summer, mosquito bites are a concern for me.

Text.SourceString: An outdoor dancing day might be fun for the kids.//What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: An outdoor dancing day might be fun for the kids.//What do you think?

Text.SourceString: The trees look beautiful today.//When I opened the windows this morning, the color was everywhere over the lake!
Text.LocalizedString: The trees look beautiful today.//When I opened the windows this morning, the color was everywhere over the lake!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> changed the kitchen soap to a brand she found on the internet. Fall limited edition – something like that. It’s shipped from Pokyo.//The whole kitchen smells like apple pie every time she does the dishes.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> changed the kitchen soap to a brand she found on the internet. Fall limited edition – something like that. It’s shipped from Pokyo.//The whole kitchen smells like apple pie every time she does the dishes.

Text.SourceString: I could stop by the hot spring to warm up tonight.//Is the hot spring working? Do you happen to know?
Text.LocalizedString: I could stop by the hot spring to warm up tonight.//Is the hot spring working? Do you happen to know?

Text.SourceString: I used <NPCName>Leah’s</> hand cream this morning. I ran out of mine. And my hands smelled like coconut the whole day.//Strong scent, that one.
Text.LocalizedString: I used <NPCName>Leah’s</> hand cream this morning. I ran out of mine. And my hands smelled like coconut the whole day.//Strong scent, that one.
